  "texts": [
    "Applying these methods results in extracting 330 features (22 body joints x 3 Coordinates x 5 statistical techniques for each joint coordinate).For the KIMORE dataset, the original dataset comprises XYZ coordinates for 25 distinct body joints, accompanied by a confidence score.",
    "This score quantifies the degree of confidence in the 3D joint position as recorded by the Kinect sensor, with values ranging from 1 (indicating a high level of confidence) to 0 (indicating a low level of confidence).",
    "Consequently, the dataset incorporates a total of 100 features.",
    "Salwa et al., [66] surveyed the most common feature extraction techniques used in human activity recognition.",
    "Instead of using only one method for feature extraction, various statistical techniques were employed, encompassing measures such as mean, median, minimum, maximum, and standard deviation, applied to each of the 100 features."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Salwa et al., [66] surveyed the most common feature extraction techniques used in human activity recognition."
